<p>GDP growth: 4.2% GDP: $27bn (PPP: $50bn) Inflation: 3.0% Population: 20.9m GDP per head: $1,310 (PPP: $2,390)</p>

<p>Poised to enter a 30th presidential year after elections in late 2011, Paul Biya's grip on power is undiminished, and the main threat he faces is from ill health (he is 79). Would-be successors will jockey for position, while the social tensions that changed regimes in north Africa simmer. Policies aimed at reducing poverty and raising employment will advance slowly, at best.</p>

